Topic : Exception Handling

Error:- A mistake in your code
Type of Error
1- Syntax Error
print("Hello')
a = 10
print("Value of"a)

An error in your code which is flaged by interpreted and will not let you
run the code is called SyntaxError.
You need to find the mistake and fix it if you want to run the code,
because you can not by pass or ignore it.

2- Runtime Error
A runtime error can not flaged by interpreter and the code will execute but
it can raise an error at run time and it can crash the program.

a = int(input("Enter A Number : "))
b = int(input("Enter B Number : "))
print("Division :",a/b)
print("Program Completed!")

this is a runtime error and this error can be handled or can be by pass or
ignore this error is also called the Exception.

3- Symmtric Error
This error can not flag by interpreter and can not raise any error at runtime
but it will not generate a desired output.

a = int(input("Enter A Number : "))
b = int(input("Enter B Number : "))
print("Addition :",a*b)  # it should be + sign
print("Program Completed!")

This type or error are called bugs and you need to find it and fix it.

Exception Handling:-
    try , except , finally

Syntax:-
try will not work alone we need to put except or finally block

try:
    write your doubtful code here
except:
    alternative code (if any error)


a = int(input("Enter A Number : "))
b = int(input("Enter B Number : "))
try:
    print("Division :",a/b)
except:
    print("Division is not Possible")
print("Program Completed!")




a = int(input("Enter A Number : "))
b = int(input("Enter B Number : "))
try:
    print("Division :",a/b)
except ZeroDivisionError as e:
    print("Error :",e)
print("Program Completed!")



Nested Except

try:
    a = int(input("Enter A Number : "))
    b = int(input("Enter B Number : "))
    print("Division :",a/b)
except ZeroDivisionError as e:
    print("Error :",e)
except ValueError as e:
    print("Error :",e)
print("Program Completed!")


try:
    a = int(input("Enter A Number : "))
    b = int(input("Enter B Number : "))
    print("Division :",a/b)
except Exception as e:
    print("Error :",e)
print("Program Completed!")



try:
    a = int(input("Enter A Number : "))
    b = int(input("Enter B Number : "))
    print("Division :",a/b)
except Exception as e:
    print("Error :",e)
finally:
    print("It will execute always")
print("Program Completed!")


